fields.title: Piano Improvisation - Fundamentals for Creating Music on the Spot
fields.about_the_course:
Have you ever wanted to be able to play anything on your piano on demand? Ever seen images by the greats and wonder how they manage to create incredible images off the top of their heads?

This course is designed to get you playing along and to give you a head start in your landscape painting journey regardless of what software you use.

No music theory required!

All you need is basic drawing skill and some inspiration. In this course, you'll overcome many of the fears and questions you've had surrounding the art of landscape painting and we'll tackle a variety of ways you can get better including:

  • Brushes to use
  • How to master composition
  • How to make your artwork look natural
  • How to use leading lines to make your painting more interesting and dynamic
  • Much more!!

This course is loosely based on landscape painting, a little bit of seascape painting on the way, but the concepts apply to painting universally. No matter what you want to be able to paint, this is a great place to start!

fields.title: Try Django: Learn and Master the Web Framework
fields.about_the_course:
What is Django?

Django is a free, open source, high-end framework written in the famously simple, flexible, and relatively easy-to-learn Python programming language.

No computer science theory knowledge required!

fields.content_description:
Welcome!

In this video, I will introduce you to Photoshop and let you know how to set up your canvas for painting.

fields.title: Be Sketchy!
fields.content_description:
Sketching!

In this video, I will introduce you to sketching and let you know how to go about it.

An image file to use as follow along has been provided to download for you.

fields.title: Color it Rough
fields.content_description:
Rough Color!

In this video, I will introduce you to colorinig and let you know how to lay down some rough colors for your painting.

If you want to know more about color, read the file content below.

Enjoy!

This class is about refining your painting.

fields.content_description: Be composited! Know angles, camera positions, one-third views, concepts and stuff

fields.content_description: This class will be solely on using the Django Rest Frame to scaffold, authenticating with DRF and so on.

fields.content_description: This class gives insight as to why testing matters, how Django handles testing, how to test models, views etc.

fields.title: Planning for Failure
fields.content_description: There are people whose sole aim is to break into your system to do good...or to cause mayhem. Either way, prepare for them.

fields.title: Setting Up - Code Editors
fields.content_description: This is the beginning part of your Django journey. I will take you through how to set up your code editors be it VS Code, Sublime Text, Brackets or whatever you want to use.

fields.content_description: Discerning the difference is the key. In this class you will understand the distinction between the two.

fields.content_description: Learn how Django models works. What CharFields, SlugField, TextField, FileField all means

fields.title: Blog App
fields.content_description: In this class, we build a blog app to show you the basic CRUD applications. CRUD means Create, Read, Update and Delete.

Amazing course! A comprehensive course to paint landscapes that'll wow.

fields.about: Hi, I am Jane Doe, Avid student of life! I love learning new things. What's great about music is that there are always new ways and things. I belive that the best way to learn is to teach. That's why I started actually. Now I teach to help others while I hone my own skills.

I have worked as a freelance Illustrator since 1993. I enjoyed doing a variety of work from being a courtroom sketch artist and animation character development artist, to illustrating corporate annual reports and children's books. I currently have illustrated books that are sold in Barnes and Noble and on Amazon.

Hello, I am Gloria and I teach Photography and styling  classes. I trained as a scientist, worked in Biotech and human vaccines, and after having my first baby, discovered the joys of Instagram and developed a new passion for photography. 7 years later, I now create beautiful imagery for designers and businesses (big and small) and help them advocate for themselves online and on social media.

Throughout her illustrious, decorated career, Mundy "The Guru as refered to by fans and clients alike has resoundingly earned her reputation as one of the most renowned recording and mixing engineers in music today, having worked with artists such as Jay-Z, Beyonce, Rick Ross, Drake, T.I., Kanye West and Eminem.

I am an author, Youtuber, and speaker who is passionate about helping students succeed. Most of my work today is done at College Info Geek - a site I created in 2010 in order to share my experience in becoming a more effective student.
Hi. I am the author of best-seller "What a Time to be Alive", an empowering call to arms for people everywhere to claim back themselves and focus on the benefits of finding oneself.

Hi, I am Tomiwa Joseph, Avid student of life! I love learning new things. What's great about code is that there are always new ways and things. I believe that the best way to learn is to teach. That's why I started actually. Now I teach to help others while I hone my own skills.

Hi, I am Theresa Rolland, Avid student of life! I love learning new things. What's great about code is that there are always new ways and things. I believe that the best way to learn is to teach. That's why I started actually. Now I teach to help others while I hone my own skills.

Hi, I am James Edmond, Avid student of life! I love learning new things. What's great about code is that there are always new ways and things. I believe that the best way to learn is to teach. That's why I started actually. Now I teach to help others while I hone my own skills.
Hi, I am a podcaster that is always evolving but forever rooted in whimsical narrative and modern graphics. I do digital paintings for a living. Welcome to my class.

I am Tangela Taylor and I make small business FUN. I want you to learn how to have fun in every aspect of your business and my classes are built around fun, actionable projects.

Ready to make your business fun? Join me!

Hi. I am Wells Jorge. I have been doing IT operations and software development for 30 years. I have worked as a Software Developer, Software Development Manager, Software Architect and as an Operations Manager.

Hi. I am Paul Andy. I have been doing IT operations and software development for 30 years. I have worked as a Software Developer, Software Development Manager, Software Architect and as an Operations Manager.

I have worked as a freelance Illustrator since 1993. I enjoyed doing a variety of work from being a courtroom sketch artist and animation character development artist, to illustrating corporate annual reports and children's books. I currently have illustrated books that are sold in Barnes and Noble and also on Amazon.

"You'd be surprised as to what learning really is"
"Being a student is easy. Learning requires actual work."
"In youth we learn; in age we understand"
